  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc5\u0db9 - \u0db1\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4\u0d94\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db0\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Colombo-Nanu Oya train removed from service",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Trains 1023 and 1024 running daily from Nanu Oya to Colombo and from Colombo to Nanu Oya will be canceled from July 01.",
        "The train will leave Nanu Oya at 6.00 am (1023) daily and reach Colombo Fort at 1.30 pm. The train will leave Colombo Fort at 12.40 pm (1024) and reach Nanu Oya at 9.20 pm.",
        "An official of the Nanu Oya Railway Station said that a large number of local and foreign tourists used to travel to Nuwara Eliya from these two trains and that many people used to travel back to Colombo by that train.",
        "According to the station masters, a large number of people used to travel to and from Watagoda, Gravat Western and Radella railway stations as there is no public transport service around all the stations from Talawakele to Nanu Oya.",
        "Trains 1023 and 1024 have been derailed and two freight trains with two compartments at the same time have been added to the service from July (01)."
      ],
